# Git Commit Rules

## Conventional Commits Scope
- Do NOT use descriptive text inside the scope of a commit message (e.g., `feat(ai): ...`).
- ONLY use the app or package name as the scope (e.g., `feat(core): ...`, `fix(web-app): ...`, `chore(docs): ...`).
- If a commit affects multiple apps, either split the commit or omit the scope (e.g., `feat: ...`) depending on the team's preference, but never invent a custom descriptive scope.
